dcterms:description: TraceLog is a large-scale heterogeneous graph dataset derived from a train ticket-based microservice system for booking training tickets. It is widely used for evaluating anomaly detection in system trace log sequences, containing four fault classes and 14 fault subclasses for different faulty types.
dcterms:title: Train Ticket Graph Dataset (TraceLog)

dcterms:description: FlowGraph is a system flow graph dataset created from heterogeneous user web browsing activities, including various scenarios such as watching videos and downloading files. It contains 600 graphs, with one attack scenario and five normal scenarios.
dcterms:title: System Flow Graph Dataset (FlowGraph)
